(Unofficial Match) 23rd May 2002
HONG KONG LEAGUE XI 0 - SCOTLAND 4  (0-2)
Referee: Ramachandran Krishnan (Malaysia) 
Goals: 0-1 Kyle 22, 0-2 Thompson 36, 0-3 Dailly 50, 0-4 Gemmill 72
Crowd: 8.000, Hong Kong Stadium, Hong Kong
HONG KONG LEAGUE XI:  Fan Chun-Yip (Chan Ka-Ki 54), Yau Kin-Wai (Lo Kai-Wah 57), Cristiano Cordeiro, 
                      Anilton Da Conceiçao (Luk Koon-Pong 33), Carlo Andre Bielemann Hartwig, Gary McKeown, 
                      Shum Kwok-Pui, Chan Ho-Man (Yeung Ching-Kwong 78), Cornelius Udebuluzor (Yeung Hei-Chi 46), 
                      Poon Yiu-Cheuk (Lee Wai-Man 78), Aderbal Filho. 
                                           
SCOTLAND:             Robert Douglas (Paul Gallacher 76), Maurice Ross (Warren Cummings 46), David Weir, 
                                   Christian Dailly [c], Allan Johnston (Gareth Williams 60), Scotland (Scot)Gemmill 
                                                   (Graham Alexander 87), Kevin Kyle (Garry O'Connor 81), Robert Stockdale, Lee Wilkie, 
                                                                 Steven Thompson (Scott Dobie 46), Scott Severin. 
                     
Notes:  Although the Hong Kong team was not a national representative team, the Scottish FA decided to award caps 
        for this match and the appearances and goals do count towards the players' totals, but the players' caps 
        of this match have not been counted in this archive.



